description: BusyBox is a multi-call binary toolset commonly used in embedded systems. Version v1.19.2 contains multiple known vulnerabilities, including command injection and privilege escalation vulnerabilities.
uClibc is a commonly used implementation of the C standard library in embedded systems. Version 1.7.0 may contain buffer overflow and integer overflow vulnerabilities.
Dropbear is a lightweight SSH server implementation. Version 2012.55 contains multiple security vulnerabilities, including CVE-2012-0920 and CVE-2012-4420.
vsftpd is an FTP server software. Version 2.3.2 has multiple known vulnerabilities, including CVE-2011-0762 and CVE-2015-1419.
